This is a clinical examination performed by a dentist or dental hygienist that consists of probing up to 28 teeth at six sites per tooth with a periodontal probe to determine prevalence of periodontal disease. This variable records for tooth Upper Right 2M (UR2M) at the distal facial (DF) site the distance from the free gingival margin (FGM) to the sulcus base (SB).
